The paper discusses the use of Scopus data to identify centers of excellence in different fields of research, which suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the visualization of performance rates, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) or cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper's focus on field-specific excellence and highly-cited papers could relate to software engineering (cs.SD).
